summary: Y’know I don’t really understand people who love Tony Stark and talk about him supporting Peter Parker and acting like a real...
body:
Y’know I don’t really understand people who love Tony Stark and talk about him supporting Peter Parker and acting like a real father figure to him.

Tony is straight up an ass. He’s got the biggest ego in the world, he’s just generally rude, and he’s super abusive. 

In Infinity War, Peter offhandedly mentions in the space-doughnut that “Technically it’s kinda your fault I’m here” and Tony makes him take it back because Tony can’t take any sort of responsibility apparently.

In Spider-man: Homecoming, Tony leaves Peter with someone who does not respect him at all or anything and ignores him and when there is an actual threat, Peter is forced to take his own action which is later punished by Iron Man even though it’s his fault he’s in the situation with no help. And later in the movie, Tony congratulates himself more than Peter saying that he made the right choice using “tough love” to make Peter’s job waaaaaaaaaay harder.

Anyway obviously I do not stan Tony Stark. He’s still abusive as shit. I mean I’m open to corrections and stuff to help me understand why people like him and why he doesn’t deserve these labels but for now this is how it is for me.

blog.title: Dream a little bigger, darling.
blog.description:
Woman.
Determined.
Braided.

What else?
Normality is overrated.
Wibbly wobbly, timey wimey.
Black, two sugars. I'll be upstairs.
One more miracle, please.

You mustn't be afraid to dream a little bigger, darling.

body:
Shirts in the MCU

so me and my friend were discussing how the shirts would be in the MCU considering how much shit has gone down there and we came up with a few ideas like:

  • YOLO doesn’t apply to me bitch
  • I survived 2 alien invasions, avoided getting dusted or crushed and ate some shawarma all in NYC

  • roses are red, violets are blue, I’m living and thriving, and I wish you were too
  • AN ALIEN INVASION…again
  • Can the aliens stop coming it’s only Monday
  • Captain America is NOT a fugitive breathe if you agree
  • can the hulk stop destroying my car? Like seriously I know you’re helping against the aliens but I just paid for my car
  • Why are the aliens invading when I’m trying to SLEEP
  • you’re under MY roof now, aliens. Prepare for war with me, bitch
  • I need way more insurance from the aliens
  • iron man should fly more bombs into the spaceships
  • three alien invasions this month and counting…
  • it’s been a long time since we saw the aliens….nevermind
  • where’s everyone


Any more ideas? I wanna see how long this gets

summary: (n.) a central nervous system stimulant of the methylxanthine class
title: (n.) a central nervous system stimulant of the methylxanthine class
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2O1l7Uk

by inkay

The engineer takes an involuntary step back. “My who is what?”

“Stark Tower. It’s haunted.” Clint scowls and crosses his arms, barely resisting the Herculean urge to stomp his foot. “Try threatening to build a Faraday cage around the coffee machine.”

“I don’t at all understand, but sure.” Stark throws his hands into the air. “If building you a giant ghost protector will stop you from doing a constant Old Man Yells At Cloud impression—”

Every single light in the room turns itself off simultaneously. Tony stares at Clint, eyes wide.

“Told you,” mutters Clint stubbornly. He notes with no small amount of trepidation that the ghost has also vanished, and the walls of the kitchen are beginning to take on an eerie glow. “Shouldn’t we do something about this?”

“Yep,” replies Tony, already dragging Clint out of the kitchen by his wrist. “Run.”

-

Clint Barton versus the ghost who can’t seem to be able to leave him alone.

summary:
Tony's hallucinations are of him from different stages of his alcoholic past:
of him drunk and dressed as doctor doom:
And of,...
body:
Tony’s hallucinations are of him from different stages of his alcoholic past:

of him drunk and dressed as doctor doom:

And of, what I think is one of the biggest causes of his alcoholism, his shitty dad:

There’s more than this and it just kills me. He’s trying to save the Earth; there should be so much on his mind to distract him, but the damn urge to drink never goes away. It overrides everything else.

Iron Man: Fatal Frontier #12
